1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:03,458
The general official was called Abu Luqman

2
00:00:03,833 --> 00:00:05,500
His name was Ibrahim al-Shawakh

3
00:00:06,416 --> 00:00:09,583
From the town of al-Sahl in Raqqa Province

4
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:11,541
The internal official

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,875
Was Mahmoud al-Ibrahim al-Dakhil

6
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:15,916
His mother’s name was Shamsa

7
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:19,750
From the town of Mansoura in the Tabqa countryside

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,500
He was originally from the al-Bou Masra clan

9
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:26,541
He was responsible for interrogations
in Tabqa and its countryside

10
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:32,458
The official in charge of the jailers was a Saudi man

11
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:35,375
Named Abu Nayef

12
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:39,875
He was responsible for the jailers and the prison’s cleanliness

13
00:00:40,083 --> 00:00:42,208
The jailers were from the same area, from Tabqa

14
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:45,750
One was called Abu Abdullah

15
00:00:46,291 --> 00:00:47,958
Another was called Abu Zaid

16
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,666
And Abdul Muin

17
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,916
And a young man nicknamed Abu Abdu

18
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:00,041
Two of them were present, and two were absent

19
00:01:00,208 --> 00:01:04,375
They took shifts for irregular periods, from days up to a week
